Here I am again after this long break I've made.... What can I say? Probably it's been a needed break or else. I've posted this design while ago at my IG account and it's the perfect time to say some more about it. The star of this design is a fantastic stamping plate I've received couple of months ago. I have always been a great fan of steampunk themed designs. When I saw BPX L023 at the store the hungry monster deep inside has been awaken. The need to try new interesting nail  art products was still alive somewhere there. And when Alice from Born Pretty Store offered me to give it a try I just couldn't resist. The plate has full pack of bold steampunk patterns  with crisp lines and magnificient details. To transfer the image on the nails was easy even for a newbie as myself. I would definitely keep working over my stamping skill because plates like this really deserve to be used more often...

The opportunity to travel is often a life-changing experience. But, travel can also be fairly stressful – both physically and mentally.New experiences and things not going quite as planned can cause feelings of fear and anxiety.This is where yoga comes in. Yoga teaches us how to breathe amidst the chaos, and it provides a space for quiet reflection amidst the noise.

When your mornings feel like this on a consistent basis, managing anxiety can feel like an uphill battle. The solution? Create a routine — and not just any routine, but one that's specifically tailored to quell stress.
We all love a good meme. These 7 yoga memes have us giggling like little school girls. Which one is your favorite?

We can’t help you with the screaming child in the aisle seat to your left, but we can help you eat well. Arrive to the gate armed with an arsenal of these nourishing, satisfying snacks, and pray the in-flight entertainment stands up to the tasty eats.

Stretching has a way of melting away stress and worry, but there's no need to unroll your yoga mat.Here are nine stretches you can do in your pajamas and your bed — either before you go to sleep or once your alarm goes off — or both! Do all nine if you have time, or just pick a few.Either way, you'll feel more relaxed, whether you're heading to the land of nod or waking with the sun.

When we declutter, we feel more organized and in control of our lives. We clear out old, stagnant energy and create space – physically and emotionally. It feels good to go through your things and make a pile of what you no longer need.Minimalism, with its foundation rooted in living with only what we need, has it right in this sense – by cleansing our space of the inevitable clutter that builds up over time, we cleanse our mental, emotional, and psychological space too.

Its not every day that you get the honour of photographing your little sister's wedding.Today we had that honour.
It doesn't get much more Swiss than this: Gruyere castle, over looking the quaint village below. Fields full of dairy cows and epic alpine mountains all around. This country is amazing.

Today marks the 6 year anniversary for the official start of Deep Blue Photography! We are currently celebrating this milestone (and both of our birthdays) with a trip to Switzerland and Iceland!We'd like to throw out a huge THANK YOU to all of our amazing clients for helping us and trusting us over the last 6 years. Without you, we would not be here today.We attempted to visit Matterhorn today, but unfortunately the weather did not cooperate, and although we reached the village at the base of the mountain, the mountain itself was completely obscured by a snowstorm.Here are a few images from the last couple of days of our time in Switzerland. So far we have visited 4 chocolatiers, hiked around a lake at a ski resort which received 30 fresh centimeters of snow the day before we arrived, visited Liechtenstein, had an amazing traditional Swiss fondue, driven almost 1000kms across an amazing country, travelled via motorail (train ferry), gondola, car, and train, and spoken 3 languages.Tomorrow we are going to geek out and visit the Large Hadron Collider at CERN, and we still have a week left in our vacation!
